The issue with the color not changing for `.container` is due to an invalid CSS custom property value. In your `style.css` file, the variable `--text-light` is defined as `#fffff` (line 3), but this is not a valid hex color code—hex colors require exactly 6 digits (e.g., `#ffffff` for white). Because of this invalid value, the `color: var(--text-light);` rule on `.container` (line 28) isn't applying, so the text color falls back to the default or inherited color (likely the dark color from `body`).

To fix this, update `--text-light` to `#ffffff`. Here's the corrected code:

```css
:root {
    --text-dark:#1b0e0e;
    --text-light:#ffffff;  /* Fixed: was #fffff */
    --bg-white: #ffffff;
}
```

This should make the color change work as expected. If you want me to apply this fix directly, let me know!

